From 0254fa0e56cb6f9b36b14afd09508355cce91810 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Aditya Kumar Singh <adisi@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 30 May 2025 12:36:04 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 5/5] wifi: ath12k: add support to handle UMAC migration HTT
 events

Once WMI Migration command is sent to firmware, it gives host back a HTT
event indicating peer migration. Host is expected to clear TID queues and
flush cache on current primary peer and set up these a fresh on the new
primary. Once done, host is expected to send HTT response event back
to firmware.

Add changes to
- handle the HTT peer migration event from firmware
- process the data and keep it ready.
- a subsequent change will do the data path changes
- send back HTT response to firmware.

Signed-off-by: Aditya Kumar Singh <adisi@qti.qualcomm.com>
Co-Developed by: Manish Dharanenthiran <mdharane@qti.qualcomm.com>
Signed-off-by: Manish Dharanenthiran <mdharane@qti.qualcomm.com>
